                <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conf. 184/242: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Commission to Negotiate Peace</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-12-01T16:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 1, 1919—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 2—1:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3934. For Polk from the Secretary of State. Your 5491 Nov. 30th 2 a.m.</p>
                <p>Jusserand on the 29th submitted Clemenceau’s request for the American
                    Commissioners to remain in Paris after the 6th. Before your telegram arrived I
                    sent the Ambassador’s note to the President and he has just replied that he
                    adheres to his original decision in regard to withdrawing of our Commissioners.
                    I have advised Jusserand of this decision and you may inform Clemenceau of it.
                    You will therefore follow out your original plan to leave on the 6th.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
